
[1]decrement

   DECREMENT, n.

   1. Decrease; waste; the state of becoming less gradually.

   Rocks and mountains suffer a continual decrement.

   2. The quantity lost by gradual diminution, or waste.

   3. In heraldry, the wane of the moon.

   4. In crystalography, a successive diminution of the lamens of
   molecules, applied to the faces of the primitive form, by which the
   secondary forms are supposed to be produced.
